&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Tiling Shell Information 
    &lt;div id=&#34;tiling-shell-information&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a Gnome Shell extension implementing modern windows tiling system by extending GNOME&amp;rsquo;s default 2 columns to any layout you want! Can be installed on Gnome Shells from 40 to 46 on X11 and Wayland: the most recent GNOME Shell is supported, and older releases will include all the features and bug fixes!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ü§© First and only extension that provides Windows 11&amp;rsquo;s snap assistant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üñ•Ô∏èüñ•Ô∏è multiple monitors support, even with different scaling factors!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;‚öôÔ∏è Manage, edit, create and delete layouts with a built-in editor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üí° Layouts are not strict, you can span multiple tiles if you want&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;üöÄ Automatically sets the same UI of your GNOME theme, for a seamless integration!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;






